President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate David Michael Satterfield as the Career Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Turkey. Satterfield, a career member of the senior Foreign Service, has been the Acting Assistant Secretary of State for Near Eastern Affairs since 2017. He has previously held various positions, including Director General of the Multinational Force and Observers in Rome, Italy, and special advisor to the Secretary of State for Libya. Satterfield is a recipient of several awards for his service.

Additionally, President Trump intends to nominate Jeffrey Byard as the Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA). Byard currently serves as the Associate Administrator for Response and Recovery at FEMA. He has extensive experience in disaster response and recovery, having served in various capacities with the Alabama Emergency Management Agency. Byard has led operations for the State of Alabama during major disasters such as Hurricane Gustav, the Deep Water Horizon Oil Spill, and the 2011 Super Outbreak. He is a former United States Marine Corps member and holds a B.S. in Business Administration.